    <summary>Security-focused systems programming language for low-level development</summary>
    <description>
Lwanga is a security-focused systems programming language designed for low-level development, shellcode creation, and penetration testing.

## Features
- Direct syscall support
- Inline assembly (Intel and AT&T syntax)
- Position-independent code generation
- Encrypted string literals
- Minimal runtime overhead
- LLVM-based native code compilation

## Tools Included
- lwangac: Compiler
- lwangafmt: Code formatter
- lwangacat: Syntax highlighter

## Use Cases
- Security research
- Penetration testing
- Shellcode development
- Low-level systems programming
- Embedded systems
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/cosmah/Project-Lwanga/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md</releaseNotes>
